<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-3103] cmake is missing RPATH on MacOSX</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-3103</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The Thrift CMakefiles do not enable RPATH handling for MacOSX.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This means that if the Thrift shared libraries are installed in a non-system directory (i.e. a directory not known by the dynamic linker), any executable linked against them will fail to run, unless the &lt;tt&gt;DYLD_LIBRARY_PATH&lt;/tt&gt; environment variable (Unix equivalent: &lt;tt&gt;LD_LIBRARY_PATH&lt;/tt&gt;) is set to the appropriate value.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;MacOSX specific&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
